---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — DevSuite"
  description="DevSuite privacy policy detailing data handling, cookies, and third-party advertising disclosures."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: June 2026</p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>Welcome to DevSuite ("we," "us," or "our"). We are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard information when you visit our website at devsuite.tools (the "Site").</p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <h3>2.1 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
    <p>When you visit our Site, our servers and third-party services may automatically collect the following information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address (anonymized where possible)</li>
      <li>Browser type and version</li>
      <li>Operating system</li>
      <li>Referring/exit pages</li>
      <li>Date and time of visit</li>
      <li>Pages viewed and time spent on pages</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2.2 Information You Provide</h3>
    <p>We may collect information you voluntarily provide, such as when you contact us via our contact page. This may include your name and email address.</p>

    <h3>2.3 Tool Usage Data</h3>
    <p>All text and data you input into our developer tools (case converter, unit calculators, etc.) is processed entirely in your browser. <strong>We do not transmit, store, or log any content you paste or type into our tools.</strong></p>

    <h2>3. Cookies & Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <h3>3.1 First-Party Cookies</h3>
    <p>We use minimal first-party cookies and local storage to remember your preferences, such as your selected theme (light or dark mode).</p>

    <h3>3.2 Third-Party Cookies (Advertising)</h3>
    <p>We use Google AdSense to display advertisements on our Site. Google and its advertising partners may use cookies and web beacons to serve ads based on your prior visits to our Site or other websites. These technologies allow Google to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Serve personalized or non-personalized advertisements</li>
      <li>Track ad impressions and user interactions with ads</li>
      <li>Prevent the same ad from being shown repeatedly</li>
      <li>Measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads Settings</a> or <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AboutAds.info</a>.</p>

    <h3>3.3 Third-Party Vendors</h3>
    <p>Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on a user's prior visits to our website. Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on visits to our Site and/or other sites on the Internet. Users may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting the Google Ads Preferences Manager.</p>

    <h2>4. How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Operate and maintain the Site</li>
      <li>Improve user experience and site performance</li>
      <li>Monitor and analyze usage patterns and trends</li>
      <li>Display relevant advertisements through Google AdSense</li>
      <li>Respond to inquiries submitted through the contact page</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Log Files</h2>
    <p>DevSuite follows standard procedures of using log files. These files log visitors when they visit websites. The information collected includes IP addresses, browser type, Internet Service Provider (ISP), date/time stamps, referring/exit pages, and the number of clicks. This information is not linked to any personally identifiable information.</p>

    <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to outside parties. This does not include trusted third parties who assist us in operating our Site (such as our hosting provider), so long as those parties agree to keep this information confidential.</p>

    <h2>7. GDPR Compliance (European Users)</h2>
    <p>If you are a European resident, you have the right to access, rectify, or delete personal data we hold about you. You also have the right to data portability and the right to restrict or object to our processing of your personal data. To exercise these rights, please contact us via our contact page.</p>

    <h2>8. CCPA Compliance (California Users)</h2>
    <p>Under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), California consumers have the right to request disclosure of data collected about them, request deletion of their data, and opt-out of the sale of their data. We do not sell personal information.</p>

    <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our Site is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information.</p>

    <h2>10. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain automatically collected log data for a maximum of 90 days. Contact form submissions are retained for up to 12 months. Theme preferences stored in your browser's local storage persist until you clear your browser data.</p>

    <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.</p>

    <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.</p>
  </article>
</MainLayout>
